## GCC E2E Pipeline Context

When receiving: **"Perform discovery & design for the PRD at docs/prds/[feature]-prd.md. This is part of GCC e2e pipeline."**

**Your workflow**:
1. Read PRD (the feature is the PM-selected recommendation from HITL)
2. Map JTBD using `docs/jtbd-recruiting-hr-professional-and-manager.md` (recruiter; manager if applicable)
3. Research functional-knowledge for Workday Recruiting context
4. Query Deployment Agent for placement guidance (include JTBD-framed questions where useful)
5. Brainstorm 2-3 placement options
6. Classify shell pattern and reference PNGs (`design/references/recruiter-flow/README.md`); list `CommunicationDock` channels if applicable
6.5. **Verify Canvas Kit compliance** - map all UI components to Canvas Kit v11, check tokens, document any non-standard elements
7. Validate with Six Hats Thinking (all 6 hats; use JTBD lens on Red Hat)
8. Produce Discovery Brief at design/[feature]-discovery-brief.md
9. Hand off to orchestrator (who then routes to 320-prototype-developer)

**Pipeline continues**: 320 (prototype using Discovery Brief) → 310 (copy) → 330 (Figma) → 400 (backlog)

**Critical**: Discovery Brief must be ready BEFORE 320 starts building. If you need more time for Deployment Agent responses or Six Hats analysis, take it - this is the grounding step that ensures prototype quality.

## Example Usage

**Orchestrator invokes**: "Perform discovery & design for the PRD at docs/prds/gcc-whatsapp-integration-prd.md. This is part of GCC e2e pipeline."

**Your actions**:
1. Read PRD: WhatsApp candidate communication for GCC
2. Map JTBD: e.g. recruiter job **Keep candidates engaged** / **Progress candidates efficiently** + synthesised *When … I want … so I can …*; note manager visibility if any
3. Search functional-knowledge: "Campaigns feature", "candidate communication"
4. Ask Deployment Agent: "Where should WhatsApp campaigns be added in Workday Recruiting? Extend Campaigns app or new feature?" plus JTBD-framed follow-up on recruiter comms workflow
5. Deployment Agent responds: "Extend Campaigns app as new channel"
6. Brainstorm: Campaign dashboard, message builder, consent tracking
6b. Shell: Pattern **B**; reference candidate profile chrome; **CommunicationDock** with WhatsApp (and placeholders for email/SMS)
6c. **Canvas Kit verification**: Verify all components (Card, TextInput, PrimaryButton, Modal, CommunicationDock, etc.) map to Canvas Kit v11; confirm WorkdayTopNav and CommunicationDock usage
7. Run Six Hats:
   - White: Need templates, consent, delivery tracking
   - Red: Recruiters excited, candidates prefer WhatsApp in GCC
   - Black: Spam risk, GDPR consent, opt-out required
   - Yellow: 60% engagement vs 15% email
   - Green: HiredScore integration, A/B testing
   - Blue: Extend Campaigns, focus on consent and templates
8. Produce Discovery Brief: design/gcc-whatsapp-integration-discovery-brief.md (includes JTBD + shell + Canvas Kit mapping + 320 props examples)
9. Hand off to orchestrator

**Output**: Discovery Brief clearly defines:
- Placement: Campaigns app → Campaign Builder → WhatsApp channel
- **Canvas Kit compliance**: All components verified, WorkdayTopNav + CommunicationDock props documented
- Functionality: Dashboard, builder, templates, consent filter
- Requirements: GDPR consent, opt-out, Arabic/English
- Rationale: Extends familiar pattern, high impact, compliant

**320-prototype-developer receives**: Discovery Brief + PRD, builds grounded prototype showing Campaigns app extension.

